15 min;35 min
Melt the butter in a large frying pan over medium heat until it is foaming.
Add the onion and garlic and cook, stirring often, until the onion is soft.
Add the livers, bay leaf, thyme and brandy or port.
Cook for 10 minutes, or until the livers are just cooked through.
Remove from the heat and cool for 20 minutes.
